1
00:00:40,150 --> 00:00:43,440
♪I don't want to hear you
nagging nonstop♪

2
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:46,790
♪Can't you just give me the result♪

3
00:00:47,100 --> 00:00:49,960
♪Don't think being older
makes you so much greater♪

4
00:00:50,170 --> 00:00:51,710
♪Just bring it on♪

5
00:00:51,910 --> 00:00:53,170
♪Watch how I'll handle you♪

6
00:00:55,200 --> 00:00:57,080
♪Hey, I'll just keep on nagging♪

7
00:00:57,080 --> 00:00:59,010
♪Keep on nagging♪

8
00:00:59,010 --> 00:01:02,030
♪You're annoying; do not get me mad♪

9
00:01:02,030 --> 00:01:05,140
♪I'm always the one
taking the blame for you♪

10
00:01:05,140 --> 00:01:08,690
♪Don't be afraid to speak;
I might hold a grudge♪

11
00:01:08,690 --> 00:01:09,970
♪No. 132♪

12
00:01:09,970 --> 00:01:10,910
♪357, what do you want♪

13
00:01:11,110 --> 00:01:12,280
♪Stop right there♪

14
00:01:13,540 --> 00:01:16,900
♪In this noisy, rowdy world,
fate is so amazing♪

15
00:01:17,060 --> 00:01:20,150
♪When we go crazy together,
joy is always with us♪

16
00:01:20,150 --> 00:01:23,260
♪We'll party till dawn♪

17
00:01:23,260 --> 00:01:26,540
♪Laughing, jumping, with no worries♪

18
00:01:26,540 --> 00:01:28,060
♪You're clearly so strange♪

19
00:01:28,060 --> 00:01:29,580
♪I'm clearly so cute♪

20
00:01:29,580 --> 00:01:32,630
♪Even if they don't get it,
it doesn't matter♪

21
00:01:32,630 --> 00:01:36,330
♪Even if it's always crazy and weird♪

22
00:01:36,330 --> 00:01:39,410
♪I still need fresh reasons for myself♪

23
00:01:42,590 --> 00:01:47,070
=Hilarious Family 2=

24
00:01:47,340 --> 00:01:50,260
=Episode 15=

25
00:01:50,550 --> 00:01:51,580
(Jiang's Noodles)
Sir,

26
00:01:51,580 --> 00:01:52,620
a bowl of fried flour.

27
00:01:53,030 --> 00:01:53,970
We don't have that.

28
00:01:55,860 --> 00:01:57,030
One bowl of butterfly noodles.

29
00:01:57,470 --> 00:01:58,410
We don't have that.

30
00:01:59,420 --> 00:02:00,360
What do you have then?

31
00:02:01,030 --> 00:02:01,970
Just plain noodles.

32
00:02:03,030 --> 00:02:04,220
I'll have one bowl.

33
00:02:04,220 --> 00:02:05,160
Alright.

34
00:02:08,140 --> 00:02:09,080
There are two of us.

35
00:02:09,700 --> 00:02:10,640
Two of us!

36
00:02:14,380 --> 00:02:15,510
This is the IOU for 200 taels

37
00:02:15,510 --> 00:02:16,850
that Long Er forced you to write.

38
00:02:20,390 --> 00:02:21,330
You...

39
00:02:24,830 --> 00:02:25,770
I'm leaving.

40
00:02:26,070 --> 00:02:27,300
Aren't you eating?

41
00:02:27,300 --> 00:02:28,270
No.

42
00:02:28,270 --> 00:02:29,210
Sixi is waiting for me.

43
00:02:29,670 --> 00:02:30,680
The noodles are for you.

44
00:02:30,990 --> 00:02:31,930
You're free now.

45
00:03:01,020 --> 00:03:01,960
Your noodles.

46
00:03:04,300 --> 00:03:05,720
Hey, I just got touched.

47
00:03:11,500 --> 00:03:15,460
(Jinyu Tea Plantation)

48
00:03:15,460 --> 00:03:17,300
What's the difference

49
00:03:17,300 --> 00:03:18,640
between fannings and scented tea?

50
00:03:20,900 --> 00:03:21,840
Fannings,

51
00:03:24,510 --> 00:03:25,450
as the name suggests,

52
00:03:26,300 --> 00:03:27,450
come from fanning trees.

53
00:03:27,740 --> 00:03:28,770
Scented tea

54
00:03:29,300 --> 00:03:31,350
comes from scented trees.

55
00:03:31,350 --> 00:03:32,330
Are you sure?

56
00:03:33,300 --> 00:03:34,840
Trees are the source of tea.

57
00:03:35,700 --> 00:03:36,740
Please.

58
00:03:36,740 --> 00:03:38,330
Even I know both teas

59
00:03:38,460 --> 00:03:39,960
come from the same tree

60
00:03:40,070 --> 00:03:41,450
and are just processed differently.

61
00:03:42,140 --> 00:03:43,670
You're running a tea shop, huh?

62
00:03:43,670 --> 00:03:44,930
No, I'm joking.

63
00:03:46,860 --> 00:03:47,800
How can you

64
00:03:47,950 --> 00:03:48,960
test me like this?

65
00:03:53,460 --> 00:03:54,890
The first bowl dries the throat.

66
00:03:55,270 --> 00:03:56,960
The second bowl kills loneliness.

67
00:03:57,300 --> 00:03:59,180
The third bowl...

68
00:03:59,260 --> 00:04:00,740
The third bowl leads to deep feelings.

69
00:04:00,740 --> 00:04:01,580
Only...

70
00:04:01,600 --> 00:04:02,490
What are you doing?

71
00:04:02,670 --> 00:04:04,070
What are you doing?

72
00:04:04,070 --> 00:04:05,740
Can't you see I'm selling tea here?

73
00:04:05,740 --> 00:04:06,830
I'm reciting a poem.

74
00:04:06,830 --> 00:04:09,050
You just can't tell what's urgent.

75
00:04:09,180 --> 00:04:10,120
Listen.

76
00:04:10,420 --> 00:04:11,460
What did you do yesterday?

77
00:04:11,620 --> 00:04:13,020
I went to Aunt.

78
00:04:13,070 --> 00:04:14,500
She asked me to bring her some meds.

79
00:04:14,550 --> 00:04:15,490
Meds?

80
00:04:16,100 --> 00:04:17,470
Why does my mother need meds?

81
00:04:17,470 --> 00:04:19,520
She said it's for beauty and skincare

82
00:04:19,820 --> 00:04:21,040
to keep the skin tight.

83
00:04:21,380 --> 00:04:22,320
Why?

84
00:04:24,060 --> 00:04:26,130
The three-month bet

85
00:04:26,130 --> 00:04:27,260
with Luo Zhusi is almost up.

86
00:04:27,270 --> 00:04:28,710
Ruan Ling and Jing Kan are not here,

87
00:04:28,710 --> 00:04:29,870
and neither of us knows tea.

88
00:04:29,880 --> 00:04:32,180
What should we do with the shop?

89
00:04:32,180 --> 00:04:33,120
Well...

90
00:04:35,620 --> 00:04:36,670
Sixi, I noticed something.

91
00:04:37,060 --> 00:04:38,000
Say it.

92
00:04:38,380 --> 00:04:39,230
Since Kan went

93
00:04:39,230 --> 00:04:40,480
to the Plantation,

94
00:04:41,500 --> 00:04:42,810
your temper has gotten worse.

95
00:04:47,150 --> 00:04:48,180
I...

96
00:04:48,180 --> 00:04:50,330
My temper has gotten worse?

97
00:04:50,500 --> 00:04:51,440
Really?

98
00:04:51,670 --> 00:04:52,610
Well.

99
00:04:53,030 --> 00:04:53,910
I have a bad temper?

100
00:04:53,910 --> 00:04:55,470
Why is my temper bad

101
00:04:55,470 --> 00:04:56,480
only with you?

102
00:04:57,230 --> 00:04:58,250
Think about it yourself.

103
00:04:59,110 --> 00:05:00,050
Think carefully!

104
00:05:01,990 --> 00:05:03,820
Isn't it because I'm the only one here?

105
00:05:03,820 --> 00:05:04,760
Only me.

106
00:05:08,910 --> 00:05:09,850
Sixi.

107
00:05:13,590 --> 00:05:14,530
Kan.

108
00:05:14,820 --> 00:05:15,760
Kan.

109
00:05:20,350 --> 00:05:21,600
Kan, you're back.

110
00:05:22,670 --> 00:05:23,650
You're back.

111
00:05:24,590 --> 00:05:25,530
Kan,

112
00:05:26,590 --> 00:05:27,890
while you were gone,

113
00:05:28,500 --> 00:05:30,010
I suffered.

114
00:05:30,550 --> 00:05:31,920
Why did you come back early?

115
00:05:32,500 --> 00:05:33,440
Because I behaved well.

116
00:05:35,230 --> 00:05:36,720
You didn't escape back, did you?

117
00:05:39,590 --> 00:05:40,530
Of course not.

118
00:05:51,300 --> 00:05:52,360
We're at the shop.

119
00:05:56,790 --> 00:05:57,710
After all this time,

120
00:05:57,710 --> 00:05:59,360
our business is still like this.

121
00:06:02,620 --> 00:06:03,860
Why are you the only one back?

122
00:06:03,860 --> 00:06:04,800
Where's Ruan Ling?

123
00:06:06,990 --> 00:06:07,960
We dragged him down.

124
00:06:08,380 --> 00:06:09,820
He suffered enough at the Plantation,

125
00:06:09,820 --> 00:06:10,760
so I let him go.

126
00:06:11,620 --> 00:06:12,560
Kan,

127
00:06:13,150 --> 00:06:14,080
Ruan Ling left,

128
00:06:14,080 --> 00:06:15,040
so who can work for me?

129
00:06:15,050 --> 00:06:16,210
Work yourself.

130
00:06:18,500 --> 00:06:19,380
But

131
00:06:19,380 --> 00:06:20,500
the bet with Luo Zhusi

132
00:06:20,500 --> 00:06:21,990
is almost due.

133
00:06:21,990 --> 00:06:23,710
You don't have anyone to help you.

134
00:06:23,710 --> 00:06:24,740
Finding another Ruan Ling

135
00:06:24,740 --> 00:06:25,680
will be tough.

136
00:06:27,110 --> 00:06:28,050
If needed,

137
00:06:28,260 --> 00:06:29,570
let Mr. An find someone.

138
00:06:31,670 --> 00:06:32,610
Excuse me.

139
00:06:33,420 --> 00:06:34,400
Are you hiring?

140
00:06:43,470 --> 00:06:45,470
Ruan Ling, Ruan Ling!

141
00:06:45,470 --> 00:06:48,040
I really suffered.

142
00:06:54,620 --> 00:06:56,110
No need to say more. I understand.

143
00:06:56,110 --> 00:06:57,050
You don't.

144
00:06:57,300 --> 00:06:58,240
Let me ask you.

145
00:06:59,060 --> 00:07:01,120
You treated me to noodles,
but why didn't you pay?

146
00:07:02,420 --> 00:07:03,360
Didn't I?

147
00:07:04,620 --> 00:07:05,910
Kan, since when

148
00:07:05,910 --> 00:07:07,010
did you two get so close?

149
00:07:07,990 --> 00:07:08,930
We shared hardships.

150
00:07:09,300 --> 00:07:10,570
I'm not soft.

151
00:07:11,260 --> 00:07:12,230
I just

152
00:07:12,230 --> 00:07:13,480
can't bear seeing

153
00:07:13,820 --> 00:07:15,160
the shop run like this.

154
00:07:15,620 --> 00:07:16,560
Got it.

155
00:07:16,940 --> 00:07:19,450
Now that you're back, I feel at ease.

156
00:07:19,990 --> 00:07:20,930
Then let's agree.

157
00:07:21,230 --> 00:07:23,260
I don't owe you money anymore,

158
00:07:23,260 --> 00:07:24,550
but if you want me to stay,

159
00:07:24,550 --> 00:07:26,280
you must agree to one condition.

160
00:07:26,910 --> 00:07:27,850
What condition?

161
00:07:28,030 --> 00:07:28,970
I want an extra bed.

162
00:07:29,110 --> 00:07:30,480
I must sleep alone.

163
00:07:30,710 --> 00:07:32,550
Also, I want a private privy.

164
00:07:32,550 --> 00:07:33,770
Only I can use it.

165
00:07:34,030 --> 00:07:35,110
So simple.

166
00:07:35,110 --> 00:07:36,450
Just a bed.

167
00:07:36,740 --> 00:07:38,040
Guiwei, go buy a bed.

168
00:07:38,250 --> 00:07:39,150
The privy?

169
00:07:39,150 --> 00:07:40,590
Guiwei, use the one outside.

170
00:07:40,590 --> 00:07:42,770
Okay, it's settled.

171
00:07:45,380 --> 00:07:46,320
Let's go.

172
00:08:02,620 --> 00:08:03,560
Grandmother.

173
00:08:09,940 --> 00:08:11,040
What's the good stuff?

174
00:08:14,180 --> 00:08:16,010
You didn't eat this as a child.

175
00:08:16,710 --> 00:08:18,670
I brought this from the Plantation.

176
00:08:18,670 --> 00:08:20,010
The people there like to eat it.

177
00:08:20,350 --> 00:08:21,600
Now, it's a delicacy?

178
00:08:22,940 --> 00:08:24,740
Seems going through hardships

179
00:08:24,740 --> 00:08:26,040
has its benefits.

180
00:08:26,740 --> 00:08:27,680
Yes.

181
00:08:28,420 --> 00:08:29,770
Let me tell you.

182
00:08:30,420 --> 00:08:31,810
Business is like war.

183
00:08:32,260 --> 00:08:33,760
If you're careless,

184
00:08:34,020 --> 00:08:35,210
you'll suffer big setbacks.

185
00:08:36,260 --> 00:08:38,000
Remember, cautiousness

186
00:08:38,350 --> 00:08:40,210
is the key to last.

187
00:08:41,620 --> 00:08:43,080
Grandmother, you used to say

188
00:08:43,080 --> 00:08:44,500
I should experience more hardships.

189
00:08:44,500 --> 00:08:45,440
I didn't understand.

190
00:08:45,660 --> 00:08:47,010
But after going to the Plantation,

191
00:08:47,010 --> 00:08:47,740
I realized

192
00:08:47,740 --> 00:08:49,240
many things in this world

193
00:08:49,500 --> 00:08:50,840
aren't as simple as I imagined.

194
00:08:52,350 --> 00:08:53,530
I just heard

195
00:08:53,860 --> 00:08:56,210
you want to participate
in the Tea Contest.

196
00:08:57,660 --> 00:08:58,600
What do you think?

197
00:09:00,780 --> 00:09:03,210
My mother made Banfang Tea

198
00:09:03,620 --> 00:09:05,320
and helped the family
win the Tea Contest.

199
00:09:05,860 --> 00:09:07,110
As her son,

200
00:09:07,110 --> 00:09:08,480
I should inherit her work.

201
00:09:09,350 --> 00:09:10,450
Also...

202
00:09:11,710 --> 00:09:13,960
Also what?

203
00:09:14,310 --> 00:09:15,250
Tell me.

204
00:09:17,350 --> 00:09:18,230
Also, I don't want

205
00:09:18,230 --> 00:09:20,210
the local tea farmers to keep suffering.

206
00:09:20,660 --> 00:09:21,960
The Plantation of Taiping County

207
00:09:22,140 --> 00:09:24,090
produces 1,600 jin of tea every year.

208
00:09:25,590 --> 00:09:26,530
Why is that?

209
00:09:27,540 --> 00:09:28,960
Because those corrupt officials

210
00:09:29,310 --> 00:09:31,240
are using this to extort and profit.

211
00:09:32,110 --> 00:09:32,950
In the end,

212
00:09:32,950 --> 00:09:34,230
it's people like us who suffer.

213
00:09:35,590 --> 00:09:36,860
The reputation of tribute tea

214
00:09:36,860 --> 00:09:37,900
may be an honor

215
00:09:37,900 --> 00:09:38,960
for Taiping County,

216
00:09:39,500 --> 00:09:41,170
but for ordinary people like us,

217
00:09:41,620 --> 00:09:42,840
it just means labor and waste.

218
00:09:43,830 --> 00:09:44,770
The ones who suffer

219
00:09:45,780 --> 00:09:46,960
are the common folk.

220
00:09:49,140 --> 00:09:50,690
The tea farmers are suffering?

221
00:09:52,500 --> 00:09:53,540
Anyway, I will definitely

222
00:09:53,540 --> 00:09:54,840
participate in the Tea Contest.

223
00:09:57,780 --> 00:09:59,330
It's good that you're ambitious.

224
00:10:01,660 --> 00:10:02,600
What pleases me most

225
00:10:03,260 --> 00:10:04,880
this time

226
00:10:05,780 --> 00:10:07,330
is not what you learned

227
00:10:07,470 --> 00:10:08,570
at the Plantation,

228
00:10:10,470 --> 00:10:12,120
but that I see someone by your side

229
00:10:12,500 --> 00:10:14,330
who never leaves you,

230
00:10:14,780 --> 00:10:17,000
sharing both hardships and joys.

231
00:10:17,900 --> 00:10:18,880
Jing Kan,

232
00:10:19,190 --> 00:10:20,530
in life,

233
00:10:20,660 --> 00:10:22,640
a good companion is rare.

234
00:10:23,710 --> 00:10:24,950
This is a blessing

235
00:10:24,950 --> 00:10:26,450
from heaven.

236
00:10:28,380 --> 00:10:30,720
You must cherish Sixi.

237
00:10:33,110 --> 00:10:34,050
I know, Grandmother.

238
00:10:45,660 --> 00:10:46,900
Didn't I tell you?

239
00:10:46,900 --> 00:10:48,470
Add more cool water to the foot bath.

240
00:10:48,470 --> 00:10:49,530
Don't make it so hot.

241
00:11:06,500 --> 00:11:07,440
Your water...

242
00:11:08,650 --> 00:11:09,620
Is the temperature okay?

243
00:11:09,620 --> 00:11:11,840
Yes. Of course, it's just right.

244
00:11:15,260 --> 00:11:16,200
Just right?

245
00:11:16,500 --> 00:11:17,440
How nice.

246
00:11:24,860 --> 00:11:25,990
Let me try it.

247
00:11:25,990 --> 00:11:26,930
Let me try the water.

248
00:11:36,110 --> 00:11:37,090
It's comfortable.

249
00:11:49,350 --> 00:11:50,810
You're sweating.

250
00:11:52,740 --> 00:11:53,690
You too.

251
00:11:57,740 --> 00:11:59,120
I use that to wipe my feet.

252
00:11:59,590 --> 00:12:01,210
It's fine, it's fine.

253
00:12:01,740 --> 00:12:03,120
The water is a bit hot.

254
00:12:03,950 --> 00:12:04,830
The water is hot.

255
00:12:04,830 --> 00:12:05,770
Really?

256
00:12:10,960 --> 00:12:11,790
Grandmother told me

257
00:12:11,790 --> 00:12:13,350
you'll participate in the Tea Contest.

258
00:12:13,350 --> 00:12:14,640
Yes, yes.

259
00:12:16,020 --> 00:12:16,960
I support you.

260
00:12:17,830 --> 00:12:18,930
Thank...Thanks.

261
00:12:20,110 --> 00:12:21,290
You won't leave again, right?

262
00:12:22,310 --> 00:12:23,640
When did I say I was leaving?

263
00:12:30,380 --> 00:12:31,410
Soaking feet as a couple?

264
00:12:32,140 --> 00:12:33,360
Why are you here?

265
00:12:34,540 --> 00:12:36,020
A letter for you delivered

266
00:12:36,020 --> 00:12:36,960
by a servant of the Ges.

267
00:12:37,230 --> 00:12:38,070
Thanks.

268
00:12:38,070 --> 00:12:39,020
Thanks, Donglin.

269
00:12:39,020 --> 00:12:40,450
Enjoy. Bye.

270
00:12:43,070 --> 00:12:44,010
What letter?

271
00:12:48,350 --> 00:12:49,720
A classmate invited me for drinks.

272
00:12:50,740 --> 00:12:52,440
They asked several times,
but I didn't go.

273
00:12:52,590 --> 00:12:53,500
You should go.

274
00:12:53,500 --> 00:12:54,440
Why not?

275
00:12:55,900 --> 00:12:57,170
I don't feel like it now.

276
00:12:57,620 --> 00:12:59,210
Though Ruan Ling is confident,

277
00:13:00,500 --> 00:13:01,600
I still feel uneasy.

278
00:13:03,430 --> 00:13:05,120
Uneasy or not,

279
00:13:05,400 --> 00:13:06,380
you should still attend

280
00:13:06,380 --> 00:13:07,600
these occasions.

281
00:13:07,860 --> 00:13:08,990
As the Chief of a shop,

282
00:13:08,990 --> 00:13:10,270
you need to interact with people,

283
00:13:10,270 --> 00:13:11,580
or how can you do business?

284
00:13:11,590 --> 00:13:13,600
- But I...
- Sixi is right.

285
00:13:13,740 --> 00:13:14,720
A merchant

286
00:13:14,990 --> 00:13:16,530
is someone who consults others.

287
00:13:16,990 --> 00:13:18,090
More friends, more options.

288
00:13:20,660 --> 00:13:21,600
How lovely.

289
00:13:22,540 --> 00:13:23,500
Close the door.

290
00:13:23,500 --> 00:13:24,440
Alright, alright.

291
00:13:32,430 --> 00:13:33,690
Tomorrow, come with me.

292
00:13:34,430 --> 00:13:35,370
Me?

293
00:13:36,590 --> 00:13:37,590
